The paper proposes a method based on deep learning for nerve segmentation in ultrasound images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of convolutional neural networks and active contour models indicates that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The paper also involves the processing of medical images, which suggests that it may be relevant to the medical imaging (cs.MS) sub-category. Finally, the use of spatiotemporal information suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
